'''Ginny''' is often used as a short form of [[Virginia]] or [[Ginevra]], and is somewhat less prone to cruel [[nicknames]]. This form of the name gaining popularity after its use as the name of the youngest [[Weasley family|Weasley]] child in the ''[[Harry Potter]]'' books, though [[J. K. Rowling]] revealed [[Ginny Weasley]]'s full name is Ginevra, not Virginia, as widely assumed, on her [http://www.jkrowling.com/textonly/en/extrastuff_view.cfm?id=7 website]. Real people named Ginny include the [[blindness|blind]] [[Christian]] singer [[Ginny Owens]],[http://www.ginnyowens.com/] and [[Ginny Brown-Waite]].

Ginny is also a derogatory slang name for [[Italian people|Italians]], and is rarely ever used as a term of endearment among Italians themselves. {{fact}}

Ginny is also the [[adjective]] for [[gin]].

